    {
      "id": "0fb8a12bdf54c19cbaf9037f9b5cd3f9dac2c245",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 160,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sebastien.buisson@bull.net",
        "username": "sebastien.buisson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-02-10 12:29:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n20% performance impact seems huge :( Maybe I would prefer the setstripe be less robust but does not have this performance penalty.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e63a05288e8bdf702665dc9479f7ef30ae16bdaa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-03-03 23:05:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(5 comments)\n\n5 style warning(s).\nFor more details please see https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Coding+Guidelines",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "5686423b512e717a43e3e0ee427a9b5615cd2a81",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-03-14 17:12:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI think that it is reasonable to make some simple layout checks on the client, but there shouldn't be a requirement that the client understand all of the potential valid and invalid parameters.  It is up to the MDS to make the final decision on acceptable parameters, since it is possible that the client and MDS are running different versions and may have different limits so the setstripe may fail even when passing the checks on the client (e.g. 2.4 client specifying a stripe count of 500 to a 2.1 MDS that has a limit of 160).\n\nInstead, I think it makes sense to avoid expensive checks on the client and instead just handle the failure in a reasonable manner, like opening the file with O_EXCL (to make sure it didn't previously exist) and deleting it afterward if the setstripe fails and leaves the file without a layout.  That would probably make sense to handle within llapi_file_create_pool(), since we don't want to delete pre-existing files.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
